    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Мало распространенное.</note>
    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">Uncommon.</note>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Корень %iaz-%i, восходя к %i*ag-%i, мог иметь закономерное развитие: %i*аg%i
        + %is-%i → %i*axš-%i, что мы и усматриваем в <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><lang/><w>āxš-</w><gloss><q>беречь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>āštīh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>āšti</w><gloss><q>мир</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>согласие</q></gloss></mentioned>, , а также в и. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_axston"/> (из %iaxs-don%i) ‘гнездо’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_axsǵiag"/> ‘любимый’; вариант %iaz-%i, с другой стороны, отложился в д.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astʼonæ"/> (из %iaz-donæ%i) ‘гнездо’. Формально %iaz-%i
        относится к %iaxs-%i, как %iaraz-%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>] к %iaræxs-%i
            [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_aræxsyn"/>], %iæmbærz-%i [<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbærzyn"/>] к %iæmbæxs-%i (*%iæmbærxs-%i) [<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>], <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*az-</w><gloss><q>гнать</q></gloss></mentioned> к <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æxsæ"/> ‘плеть’, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*ā-haz-</w><gloss><q>хватать</q></gloss></mentioned> к <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_axæssun"/> ‘ловить’. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_axsǵiag"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The root %iaz-%i, going back to %i*ag-%i, could have a natural development:
        %i*аg%i + %is-%i → %i*axš-%i, что мы и усматриваем в <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>āxš-</w><gloss><q>cherish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>āštīh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>āšti</w><gloss><q>peace</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>consent</q></gloss></mentioned>, , and also in Iron <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/> (from %iaxs-don%i) ʽnest’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_axsǵiag"/> ‘favourite’; the variant %iaz-%i, on the other hand, developed
        into Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astʼonæ"/> (from %iaz-donæ%i) ‘nest’. Formally,
        %iaz-%i relates to %iaxs-%i, like %iaraz-%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>] to
        %iaræxs-%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_aræxsyn"/>], %iæmbærz-%i [<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbærzyn"/>] to %iæmbæxs-%i (*%iæmbærxs-%i) [<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>], <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*az-</w><gloss><q>drive</q></gloss></mentioned> to <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æxsæ"/> ‘lash’, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*ā-haz-</w><gloss><q>grab</q></gloss></mentioned> to <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_axæssun"/> ‘catch’. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"/>, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_axsǵiag"/>.</etym>
</entry>
